text: Shanah Tovah to all those celebrating in Southern California and beyond! Wishing you a sweet new year of peace, happiness, and good health. https://t.co/Imiks5MkrQ

Soaring grocery prices and historic cuts to food assistance enacted in H.R. 1 are making it harder than ever for SoCal families to keep food on the table. Now, the Trump Administration is ending USDA’s annual hunger report, blurring the picture of how food insecurity is really impacting everyday Americans. We can’t fight hunger by hiding it. Our hard-working families deserve better. https://t.co/S4bkUdI6WH

🚨TOMORROW: Join my team for our first-ever passport fair! Navigating the passport process can be challenging, but my office is here to help. My team will be on-site at the Buena Park Library with folks from the Department of State tomorrow, September 20, from 9 AM to 3 PM to answer any questions you may have about the passport process and provide assistance with your application. Appointments are not required but are recommended, as walk-ins will be assisted on a first-come, first served basis. Please visit https://t.co/c6NlI8PDLA to make your appointment today.

Democrat or Republican, costs are simply too high for all Americans. I joined my colleagues on the Lowering Costs Caucus to urge Speaker Johnson to stop playing political games and address the affordability crisis so we can deliver real economic relief for families across the country.

My parents fled communist Vietnam, where free speech and political opposition are punished. They came to America because the right to free speech is paramount. Political violence is abhorrent and incompatible with American values. I voted in favor of the Charlie Kirk resolution because, no matter our differences, violence is never the answer to political disagreement. I deeply disagree with the views that Kirk held and the positions he advocated, but that does not change the fact that his murder was a needless tragedy. There is no place for hate in our politics. There is no place for violence in our politics. We must work together to lower the temperature and find common ground.

I’m always thrilled to welcome folks from CA-45 to my office in DC! I was grateful for the chance to meet with Richard, Colin, and Kyla from Garden Grove to hear about groundbreaking research to find a cure for spinal muscular atrophy. https://t.co/jimbkfjFm0

I joined my colleagues in calling on House leadership to permanently extend the ACA tax credits, and I cosponsored the Protecting Healthcare and Lowering Costs Act to put more money back in your pocket and preserve your access to high-quality, affordable health care.

When Congressional Republicans passed H.R. 1, they voted to end health care premium tax credits through the Affordable Care Act. Now, Californians are about to see their premiums spike by over 10% – that’s unacceptable. https://t.co/XlEbnv9WLB

Are you a high school student or graduate under age 23 interested in attending one of our prestigious service academies? Keeping our communities safe will always be my priority. I'm proud to join @RepLauraGillen to urge leadership to prioritize federal support for local law enforcement in any government funding package.

Minority-serving institutions play a crucial role in educating our community, helping to uplift future leaders from all walks of life. I met with leaders from five of CA-45’s MSIs to discuss how President Trump’s drastic funding cuts to MSIs will impact our local students. I’m committed to preserving equitable access to education that allows every student to grow and thrive.

As the dad of three young kids, I know how hard it can be to juggle work and raising a family. On National Working Parents Day, and every day, I’m committed to delivering common-sense solutions that lower costs and help our hard-working families thrive.

I was honored to join the Congressional Hispanic Conference and @HispanicCaucus to support of the construction of the Museum of the American Latino. I’m always proud to celebrate the rich history and countless contributions of our Hispanic and Latino communities. https://t.co/50AqiEY007

Access to essential healthcare is non-negotiable for all California families – and that includes quality at-home, telehealth, and hospice care. It was great speaking with dedicated folks from the National Alliance for Care at Home about how I can support their mission to make high-quality home care affordable and accessible for our community members.

Congressional Republicans passed legislation that eliminates the Affordable Care Act’s premium tax credits, spiking costs for Californians by $2,500 annually. That’s unacceptable. I’m proud to cosponsor the Protecting Healthcare and Lowering Costs Act to permanently extend the ACA’s premium tax credits and defend affordable health care access for our community members. https://t.co/png1qiIOAZ

Parkinson’s disease affects so many Americans across the country – but dedicated folks with the Michael J. Fox Foundation for Parkinson’s Research are working hard to find a cure. It was great speaking with Jennifer, Rebecca, Larry, and Luis today about how I can support the funding and research necessary to fight Parkinson’s disease.

I’m deeply concerned by the Trump Administration’s decision to end funding for minority-serving educational institutions. Equitable access to education for all Americans fosters innovation and essential global leadership. I'm committed to ensuring that every student, no matter their background, has access to the educational opportunities that will help them thrive.

This is horrifying. Political violence is abhorrent and unacceptable. My thoughts and prayers are with Charlie and his family.

Tariffs are costing small businesses and consumers millions of dollars, and we don't even know where the next price hike will come from. We owe our former servicemembers an immense debt of gratitude for their service – and we can show it by fully funding the programs Veterans and their families rely on. I was honored to meet with Maryann, Tim, and Livy, American heroes with Veterans of Foreign Wars, to discuss how I’m fighting for the folks who fought for us.

Orange County is consistently ranked one of the most expensive places to live in our country – and it's getting harder and harder for working families to buy a home. I’m proud to cosponsor the bipartisan Affordable Housing Credit Improvement Act of 2025 because stable, affordable housing is a non-negotiable for every SoCal family.

Estoy profundamente decepcionado y alarmado por la decisión de la Suprema Corte que permite a los agentes del gobierno aplicar las leyes de inmigración utilizando perfiles raciales discriminatorios. Esta decisión debilita descaradamente los derechos consagrados en la Cuarta Enmienda de la Constitución y amenaza nuestras libertades constitucionales.

Como hijo de inmigrantes, entiendo el verdadero miedo que tantos en nuestra comunidad ahora tienen. Atacar a miembros de nuestras comunidades que tratan de vivir en paz en nuestro país no nos hace más seguros – necesitamos una aplicación inteligente de la ley de inmigración que se enfoque en criminales violentos que realmente amenazan la seguridad pública. Le ruego a nuestros vecinos a través de California que se mantengan seguros y se comuniquen con mi oficina si necesita ayuda.

I’m deeply disappointed and alarmed by the Supreme Court’s decision that allows government agents to conduct immigration enforcement using discriminatory racial profiling. This move brazenly undermines rights enshrined in the Fourth Amendment and threatens our Constitutional freedoms.

As the son of immigrants, I understand the true fear that so many in our community now face. Targeting law-abiding members of our communities living peacefully in our country does not make us safer – we need smart immigration enforcement that focuses on violent criminals who truly threaten public safety. I encourage our neighbors across California to stay safe and to contact my office if you need assistance.  https://t.co/yO0B7naAsy

Need help with a federal agency? From Social Security benefits to emergency passports, my office is here for you. For assistance, please call (714) 960-6483 or visit https://t.co/iEYnCoZStK. https://t.co/XChr5JV0ZX

President Trump's budget threatens health care coverage for over 80,000 children in our community. That’s not OK with me. I introduced the Keep Kids Covered Act to ensure that every child covered by Medicaid has affordable access to the quality health care they need.

The United States is a beacon of freedom and democracy across the globe. We must honor that commitment and press Israel to allow robust humanitarian aid and reach a ceasefire in Gaza. Palestinians and Israelis deserve to live in security and dignity; U.S. materiel support to its allies and partners should reflect that.

I’m grateful to the on-site troops who rushed toward danger to secure the suspect, and to the first responders who continue to be heroes treating victims and arresting the suspect. My heart is with the victims, their families, and all others impacted by this senseless act of violence.

In the middle of the night, passed through a procedural trick instead of a normal process, House Republicans jammed through President Trump’s effort to slash billions of dollars from critical public media, often the only reliable source of emergency response information in many communities. This reckless move will strip access to essential news and information away from millions of families around the country. The Trump Administration is also continuing to slash foreign aid initiatives that save millions of lives. This move will cede more global influence to China and Russia, threatening our national security. I voted NO on this reckless legislation. I came to Washington to serve my community, and I’ll keep working tirelessly to secure the resources we need to thrive.

In the past 50 years, members of the Vietnamese diaspora–including my own parents–have rebuilt their lives around the world, bringing with them a vibrant culture and a resounding spirit of resilience. From the ashes of war, we have emerged as today’s trailblazers and community leaders–a testament to our strength and determination.

I was glad to welcome @RepGraceMeng, @RepJudyChu, @RepZoeLofgren, and @RepLiccardo as they joined me today in recognizing Black April.  The fall of Saigon in 1975 left an indelible mark on the lives of generations of Vietnamese families. Fifty years later, the Vietnamese diaspora has thrived. I was honored to stand before our nation’s Capitol to share our story.

The fall of Saigon forced hundreds of thousands of Vietnamese families from their homes, many of whom risked their lives searching uncharted waters for liberation abroad. Today, I reflect on the courage of the Boat People, and pay tribute to those who perished at sea. Their sacrifices will not be forgotten.

Today marks the 50th anniversary of Black April, known as Tháng Tư Đen in Vietnamese. I’m proud to stand with my community in solemn remembrance of the lives lost in the mass exodus following the fall of Saigon, and in honor of the former Republic of Vietnam veterans and U.S. veterans who fought bravely alongside each other to uphold freedom and democracy.

This week, in commemoration of the 50th anniversary of the fall of Saigon, known as Black April, I will be hosting a series of events in Washington to share stories of immense courage, sacrifice, and resilience of the Vietnamese diaspora. Stories of Vietnamese families forced to flee their homeland, embarked on perilous journeys, determined to escape oppression and persecution. As the only Vietnamese American Member of Congress, and the first to represent the world’s largest Vietnamese diaspora, I take great pride in showcasing our heritage flag in front of my office in Washington--representing the ideals of freedom and liberty.

I enlisted in the U.S. Army when I was 18 years old, and my education was sponsored by the GI Bill. I owe my career to the support I received in exchange for my service.
